I aligned Product/Data/Eng on a single success metric, drove a quick instrumentation plan, and ran a short discovery sprint to identify the top friction points. I then owned the delivery of two targeted changes (simplified steps + clearer in-product guidance) and set up a weekly operating cadence for iteration. Result: meaningful drop in drop-off and faster time-to-value, with a clear measurement plan and follow-ups owned.

2) Execution + judgment under constraints (tradeoffs, pragmatic decisions): In a time-sensitive release, we had to choose between a “perfect” architecture and a reliable incremental solution. I proposed a phased approach: ship a safe MVP with guardrails and monitoring, then iterate toward the longer-term design once we had usage data. I coordinated with stakeholders on scope cuts, communicated risks transparently, and ensured QA/rollout readiness. Result: shipped on time with low incident rate and a clear path to the next iteration.

If helpful, I can provide deeper specifics (scope, metrics, and my exact responsibilities) in the next step. I’m very interested in moving forward quickly and am ready to commit to the process.
